Probably the 50s and 60s, in many ways, were kind of 
a peak period for the city of Austin. There was a lot

28:40.859 --> 28:46.166
of self-confidence, and we weren't that 
sensitive to some of the problems that existed. It

28:47.348 --> 28:57.422
was no big deal that certain parts of Boston had 
flooding problems and that certain people didn't

28:47.348 --> 28:57.422
live very well or had very inadequate houses, or 
their incomes were extremely low. So I think a lot

28:58.403 --> 29:06.074
of the sensitivity that we're aware of in terms of 
our problems today, we just didn't have back then.

29:06.094 --> 29:07.896
But if we really look back at it, And for some 
people, it really wasn't that good a period. So

29:11.343 --> 29:15.210
there's a lot of trade-offs in every community. 
And I think that Austin is facing those today. In a

29:22.685 --> 29:24.408
way that they've never had in the past. In a way that 
they've never had to do in the past. This creates a

29:29.138 --> 29:31.401
lot of concern. There's a lot of people that feel 
like they're losing status and position. There's

29:35.967 --> 29:38.771
a much greater turmoil and changeover. You've got 
major industries coming into town that are

29:39.712 --> 29:48.944
beginning to employ people for, if not decent 
wages, at least certainly adequate wages. TI,

29:50.687 --> 29:56.074
Westinghouse, Motorola, IBM. or major employers 
in town. And they, although don't pay at the scale

29:58.683 --> 30:08.616
they do in St. California, they are certainly 
paying above what has been the tradition in the

29:58.683 --> 30:08.616
service industries associated with Austin. So, 
you know, you begin to see people having

30:10.639 --> 30:15.245
opportunities in Austin. It's not a matter of if 
you lose your job with the city or Texas University

30:15.825 --> 30:25.658
or the state bureaucracy that you're suddenly 
forced to necessarily leave town. Mm-hmm. There

30:26.547 --> 30:41.041
are many departments at Texas that are just 
frantic because they can't keep the people

30:26.547 --> 30:41.041
employed because the people were committed to 
living in Austin, but suddenly they find they can

30:26.547 --> 30:41.041
make what they're worth by going across the street 
